    "body": "@jreback, is frame really transposed? I mean, rows should be records and columns should be record fields, right?\n\nRow-based creation from dictionaries is accomplished by `pd.DataFrame.from_dict(d, orient='index')`.\n\nRow-based creation from series is inefficient because all series elements share the dtype (in this example â€” `object`) and have to be cast back with `frame.convert_objects` to win back native efficiency for numeric and datetime/timedelta fields. Performance-wise, if the data comes with records being series, there should be not much penalty in transposing the frame after construction.\n"
  },
